ems excluded from ridership table ==\n\nThe following [[light rail]] systems have been excluded from the ridership table above:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:150px;\"| System\n! Largest city served\n! Opened\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Route length\n! style=\"width:600px;\"| Reason(s) for exclusion from Ridership table\n|-\n| [[Galveston Island Trolley]]\n| [[Galveston, Texas|Galveston, TX]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1988<ref name=\"GIT\">{{cite web | title = Island Transit Information | publisher = Island Transit | url = http://www.islandtransit.net/info.htm | date = | access-date = 2013-08-21}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{convert|6.8|mi|km}}<ref name=\"GIT\" />\n| Galveston's [[heritage streetcar]] trolley system is ''non-operational'' \u2013 it has suspended its service since September 2008 due to damage from [[Hurricane Ike]].\n|-\n| [[Streetcars in Kenosha, Wisconsin|Kenosha Streetcars]]\n| [[Kenosha, Wisconsin|Kenosha, WI]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2000<ref name=\"Kenosha-Streetcar\">{{cite web | title = Streetcar Route Map | publisher = Kenosha Streetcars Today | via = http://www.kenoshastreetcarsociety.org/today | url = http://www.kenosha.org/kenevents/graphics/pdf/Streetcar_Route.pdf | format = PDF | year = | access-date = 2013-07-14}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{convert|2.0|mi|km}}<ref name=\"Kenosha-Streetcar\" />\n| This [[heritage streetcar]] system is primarily a ''tourist'' system (e.g. does not operate daily, year-round), rather than a transit system; Kenosha's transit systems are too small to be tracked by APTA.\n|-\n| [[Metro Streetcar]]\n| [[Little Rock, Arkansas|Little Rock, AR]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2004<ref name=\"River-Rail\">{{cite web|title=River Rail \u2013 Central Arkansas Transit Authority |publisher=[[Central Arkansas Transit Authority]] (CATA) |url=http://www.cat.org/river-rail |access-date=2013-08-18 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902085256/http://www.cat.org/river-rail |archive-date=2013-09-02 }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{convert|3.4|mi|km}}<ref name=\"River-Rail\" />\n| This [[heritage streetcar]] system is primarily a ''tourist'' system, rather than a transit system; APTA does not provide ridership figures for this system.\n|-\n| [[River Street Streetcar]]\n| [[Savannah, GA]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2009\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{convert|1.0|mi|km}}\n| This [[heritage streetcar]] system is primarily a ''tourist'' system, rather than a transit system; APTA does not track this system.\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{div col|colwidth=35em}}\n* [[Light rail in the United States]]\n* [[Light rail]]\n* [[List of North American light rail systems by ridership]]\n* [[Light rail in North America]]\n* [[Streetcars in North America]]\n* [[List of tram and light rail transit systems]]\n* [[List of rail transit systems in the United States]]\n* [[List of United States rapid transit systems by ridership]]\n* [[List of North American rapid transit systems by ridership]]\n* [[List of Latin American rail transit systems by ridership]]\n* [[List of United States commuter rail systems by ridership]]\n* [[List of United States local bus agencies by ridership]]\n* [[Public transportation]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Reflist|group=\"note\"}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Light rail in the United States|*]]\n[[Category:United States railway-related lists|Rail systems by ridership]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{See also|List of North American light rail systems by ridership|List of United States rapid transit systems by ridership}}\n{{Use mdy dates|cs1-dates=ly|date=April 2020}}\nThe following is a '''list of all [[light rail]] systems in the United States, ranked by ridership.'''  Also included are those urban [[tram|streetcar/trolley]] systems that are providing regular public transit service (i.e. operating year-round and at least five days/week). This list does ''not'' include statistics for [[Rapid transit|metro/rapid transit]] systems (see: the [[List of United States rapid transit systems by ridership]] for those). Daily and annual ridership figures are based on \"average weekday ''unlinked'' passenger trips\" (where transfers between lines are counted as two separate passenger \"boardings\" or \"trips\"). The annual ridership figures for 2019 and average weekday ridership figures for the fourth quarter (Q4) of 2019 come from the [[American Public Transportation Association]]'s (APTA) Ridership Reports statistics for the fourth quarter (Q4) of 2019,<ref name=\"APTA-2019-Q4\" /> unless otherwise noted (e.g. [[NJ Transit]] systems).  References with supplementary (i.e. non-APTA) ridership figures are included in the ''System'' column.\n\n== List ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin: 1em auto 1em auto;\"\n|-\n!\n! style=\"width:250px;\"| System\n! Largest city<br />served\n! Annual<br />Ridership<br /><small>(2019)</small><ref name=\"APTA-2019-Q4\">{{cite web | url = https://www.apta.com/wp-content/uploads/2019-Q4-Ridership-APTA.pdf | title = Transit Ridership Report Fourth Quarter 2018 | publisher = [[American Public Transportation Association]]| format = PDF | via = https://www.apta.com/research-technical-resources/transit-statistics/ridership-report/ridership-report-archives/ | date = February 27, 2020 | access-date = 2020-04-04}}</ref>\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Avg. daily<br />weekday<br />boardings<br /><small>(Q4 2019)</small><ref name=\"APTA-2019-Q4\" />\n! style=\"width:55px;\" data-sort-type=\"number\"| System<br />length\n! Avg. daily<br />boardings<br />per mile<br /><small>(Q4 2019)</small>\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| Year<br />opened\n! style=\"width:40px;\" data-sort- type=\"number\"| Stations\n! style=\"width:40px;\" data-sort- type=\"number\"| Lines\n! Year<br />last<br />expanded\n|-\n| 1\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Metro Rail (Los An